Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with 1/4 tsp of @salt{1/4%tsp} for
the rice. When boiling, add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12%minutes}.
Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{}.

Meanwhile, heat a glug of @oil{glug} in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat.
While the pan gets hot, put the @Cornflour{10%g} in a large #bowl{} and season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the @Diced Chicken Breast{260%g} to the bowl and
toss to coat completely in the cornflour.

> Wash your hands after handling raw chicken.

Once the oil is hot, add the chicken to the pan and stir-fry until golden brown,
~{4-5%minutes}.

While the chicken cooks, halve, peel and thinly slice the
@Echalion Shallot{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Trim the @Green Beans{150%g}
and chop into thirds. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and grated),
or use a #garlic press{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in another large frying pan on a medium high
heat. Once hot, add the @Baby Corn, Greens & Carrots{200%g} and stir fry for
~{2-3%minutes}. Then add a splash of @water{Splash}, cover with a #lid{} (or some
#foil{}) and steam-fry until the veggies are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove the
pan from the heat.

Once the chicken is browned, add a drizzle of oil if you need to, add the
shallot, cook with the chicken until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in the
garlic and @Tomato Puree{30%g}, cook for ~{1%minute}. Pour in the
@Water{150%ml for the Sauce}, @Chicken Stock Powder{1}, @Honey{45%g} and
@Soy Sauce{25%g}.

Stir in the green beans, bring to a simmer. Cover with a lid or some foil,
simmer until the beans are cooked and the sauce has thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Once the chicken and beans are cooked, taste and add salt and pepper if you
feel it needs it.

> The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add a splash more water if you feel it needs it.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}. Spoon into #bowls{} and top with the soy
honey chicken. Serve the rainbow mix on top (reheat first if necessary!) and
enjoy!